In this press gaggle, Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton addresses various topics including Goldman Sachs' earnings, Greg Craig taking a job at Goldman Sachs, the President's upcoming speech on financial reform, "don't ask, don't tell," immigration, D.C. voting rights, the President's visit to New York, regulatory reform, the volcanic ash affecting Americans abroad, North Korea's atomic weapons, and Rahm Emanuel potentially running for mayor of Chicago. Overall, Burton emphasizes the need for financial reform and the President's commitment to addressing various issues. He also mentions that the President thinks highly of Rahm Emanuel as Chief of Staff.